get.description:
Upgrades to a WebSocket connection for live bid/ask ticks. Not all MT5 servers support live tick streaming. If this endpoint is not supported for your account, please contact support.

### Client messages
Send JSON text frames after the WebSocket is connected. The only supported incoming message is `subscribe`.

Each `subscribe` replaces the complete active symbol list for the connection. A single `subscribe` message can include at most 100 symbols. Send `{"type":"subscribe","symbols":[]}` to clear subscriptions.

```json
{"type":"subscribe","symbols":["EURUSD","XAUUSD"]}
```

### Server messages
All outgoing messages are JSON text frames with a `type` discriminator.

- `connection.ready`: sent once after the socket is accepted.
- `subscription.updated`: sent after a valid `subscribe` message is applied.
- `tick`: sent for subscribed symbols when bid and ask are both available.
- `error`: sent when the server rejects a message or cannot process the subscription.

```ts
type ServerMessage =
  | ConnectionReadyMessage
  | SubscriptionUpdatedMessage
  | TickMessage
  | ErrorMessage;

type ConnectionReadyMessage = {
  type: "connection.ready";
  accountId: string;
  requestId: string;
  symbols: string[];
  heartbeatSeconds: number;
};

type SubscriptionUpdatedMessage = {
  type: "subscription.updated";
  accountId: string;
  symbols: string[];
};

type TickMessage = {
  type: "tick";
  accountId: string;
  symbol: string;
  bid: number;
  ask: number;
  spread: number;
  timestamp: string;
  time: number;
  time_msc: number;
  flags: number;
};

type ErrorMessage = {
  type: "error";
  code: string;
  message: string;
  symbol?: string;
};
```
